HEADWORD: Scrapple
<hw>Scrap"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. of
<ets>scrap</ets>.]</ety> <def>An article of food made by boiling
together bits or scraps of meat, usually pork, and flour or Indian
meal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

